{% extends 'base.html.twig' %}

{% block title %}{{ title }} - My Framework App{% endblock %}

{% block body %}
<div style="text-align: center; padding: 3rem 0;">
    <h1 style="font-size: 3rem; margin-bottom: 1.5rem; color: #2c3e50;">{{ title }}</h1>
    <p style="font-size: 1.25rem; color: #7f8c8d; margin-bottom: 2rem;">{{ message }}</p>
    
    <div style="max-width: 800px; margin: 0 auto; text-align: left;">
        <h2 style="font-size: 1.75rem; margin-bottom: 1rem;">What is this?</h2>
        <p>This is a complete web framework built from scratch, inspired by Symfony's architecture. It demonstrates:</p>
        
        <ul style="margin: 1rem 0 2rem 2rem; line-height: 2;">
            <li><strong>HTTP Foundation</strong> - Request/Response abstraction</li>
            <li><strong>Routing</strong> - URL matching and parameter extraction</li>
            <li><strong>HTTP Kernel</strong> - Request handling workflow</li>
            <li><strong>Dependency Injection</strong> - Service container and autowiring</li>
            <li><strong>Event System</strong> - Observer pattern for extensibility</li>
            <li><strong>Controller Resolution</strong> - Automatic controller instantiation</li>
            <li><strong>Argument Resolution</strong> - Auto-inject dependencies and parameters</li>
            <li><strong>Templating</strong> - Twig integration</li>
        </ul>

        <h2 style="font-size: 1.75rem; margin-bottom: 1rem;">Try it out!</h2>
        <p style="margin-bottom: 1rem;">
            Visit the <a href="/blog" style="color: #3498db; text-decoration: none; font-weight: 600;">Blog</a> 
            to see the framework in action.
        </p>

        <div style="background: #ecf0f1; padding: 1.5rem; border-radius: 6px; margin-top: 2rem;">
            <h3 style="margin-bottom: 0.5rem;">Quick Start</h3>
            <pre style="background: #2c3e50; color: #ecf0f1; padding: 1rem; border-radius: 4px; overflow-x: auto;"><code>// Start the development server
php -S localhost:8000 -t public/

// Visit in browser
http://localhost:8000
http://localhost:8000/blog
http://localhost:8000/blog/1</code></pre>
        </div>
    </div>
</div>
{% endblock %}
